place_description: Seattle-based coffeehouse chain known for its signature roasts, light bites and WiFi availability.

reviews_data.review_text: In and out quickly!

It's 6:09am. They are supposed to open at 5:30am, but are not. The people inside tell me they are not sure when they will open because they are still counting the cash register. Honestly, this is the typical Starbucks now.
You walk in this store, and they will just look at you, give no greeting, and just say what you would like.
Good

This is the 3rd Saturday in a row that the drive through has been shut down. Today they had 6 workers inside so you can't use the excuse of "we didn't have enough employees to work"  It took 30 minutes inside to order 1 drink and leave. This used to be our regular Starbucks, but not anymore.  Poor management.
They don't call names over the audiospeakers if you're not near the front
Great Customer Service
Great
Went to get coffee and relax before work but apparently they only do drive through now... sigh on door with no explanation why you can't walk in there now...
Friendly service and drink tasted great.
Super friendly and fast service. Made my order to perfection and tasted great.

I used to come to this location out of convenience to my job and stopped but couldn't remember why.  I went to this location for first time in awhile and instantly remembered why I don't  come... my coffee is never hot it's always barely lukewarm. Please fix this
Coffee was good. Clean store, good staff
Great service
Came in for an oatmilk Expresso. Asked if it had dairy and they assured me it didn't. Well it definitely did and I'll it's now going to mess up my entire day.

I ordered the Lavender Frappuccino on the app and went to the drive thru, it took some more time to get my order like 10min or so. Service was kinda slow that day and there were only 2 cars ahead. I enjoyed my drink though.

I ordered Chai tea latte and it was terrible.I felt like I am drinking a boiled water.There was no chai taste.I earlier had chai tea latte in other star buck's and it was pretty good but not sure why it was so bland here.

I love the Brown Sugar Oatmilk Shaken Espresso  with..
Dark caramel sauce on the bottom
Salted caramel cream foam
Topped with a caramel swirl
Somewhere between the void of time and the paragon of oblivion is the iced coffee that I ordered here.

In this location you need a code to use the restroom which is understandable. the issue is the length and complexity of the code, an elderly or a person with cognitive issues will not be able to remember it by the time they get to the restroom. Pretty sad.

Repost, 2 months later and NOTHING has changed?? .I am considered a regular at this particular location usually I get one to two orders a day Monday through Friday. The morning crew is outstanding phenomenal but, The night and weekend crew is horrific. I have spoken with Management on more than one occasion in regards to the service doing this time.

Today was the last day that I will patronize this location at night or on the weekend and I will not recommend anybody to come to this location after 5:00 pm MONDAY through FRIDAY..

Save your time and money and go to another location after 5 pm and all weekend.

I went to Starbucks to get my usual, grande caramel ribbon crunch, extra caramel drizzle with a shot of espresso when I got to the window the African-American girl asked for my payment. I told her I was paying with points she left the window, went over to the Caucasian girl who was making my drink, who then put the drink down got a new cup, filled my cup up with half whipped cream, and then proceeded to make the drink and put more whip cream at the top basically the drink was whip cream with minimal drizzle never going back mind you you have to spend $200 to even get a grande frappe with points poor customer service racial discrimination do not recommend !
Great cold brew

Was in today to work while my car was serviced at Costco across the parking lot. With zero warning, at 11 am after I just ordered a coffee and sat down to work, the employees told us they were closing the lobby and to leave, with seemingly no explanation or warning. Terrible service. Would've been nice to have a heads up.

Busy location, employees are working hard but don't go out of their way like other locations. My preferred drink is a Ventin Flat White, often it's served with a head of foam. So not a Flat White... and like today, not even filled.

I came to finish work. I looked online and saw it closed at 9pm. We were told by the worker she was locking up in 10 minutes but the outside is still open. It is 7pm and they are already closed. If you are closing at 7p then you need to state that on the door and online. I will not be coming back here again.
Poor service & bad attitudes.

Terrible.
Chai latte tasted like water. Banana bread they offered to "warm" was basically frozen. Has to be the worse Starbucks location in Charlotte.

I stop by everytime I go to Costco and they 100% everytime mess up my drink order or give me something completely different that's not what I ordered. I Went inside to get it fixed and was given attitude and was told " well if you want another drink it'll be 20 minutes" I've got my point and will never come back, staff sucks and clearly need to be retaught on how to make the drinks they're making.
They never add my extra things I pay for but the morning crew is nice.

This Starbucks is beyond busy.  We waited over 15 minutes in the drive through before coming in to order. It was just as packed as the drive through.  They no longer make or sell medicine ball tea - shame on you Starbucks for stopping that product! We waited nearly 30 minutes inside and the pastry we ordered came 10 minutes after our coffee order. I will not return to this location.
Their inside was closed so had to go through drive thru. Pleasant & fast experience. Great customer service.
Always, the Best Hot  coffee
Our drinks are amazing when we go at 6:30a
This location needs to replace the glass in their menu signs in the drive thru.
It's my neighborhood Starbucks that I work there from time to time..foods and drinks are typical 'Starbucks'.. staffs are decent and friendly
Thank you for being here. The vibes are great I appreciate you the bathroom break. You guys are awesome.
Great coffee. Super drive thru service

Terribly slow service and the employees don't seem to care.  Location is clearly understaffed from the mobile order demand and demand from the Costco across the parking lot.  Waited over 30 minutes for one drink.  Last time I'm visiting this Starbucks.
Says it's closed at 9... got to the Starbucks. They close at 8
They were very knowledgeable with the new fall drinks and helpful in making a selection. Great service
Best Starbucks around!!!
Completely unable to handle the morning rush.  Inexcusable to have mobile pick ups take the back seat to the drive through.
This particular Starbucks point seriously does not know how to prepare a proper coffee.! The white choco mocha was the worst that I have ever tasted in this branch.
had a great experience at this store- they're friendly, organized, working well!
Great place to eat and work. Lots of tables with access to charging.  It's loud, but that's expected.  Clean and roomy.
Food was not heated enough. Didn't tell barista though. Manageable to eat. They had nice staff, if mentioned they would have checked and corrected.
Great service, friendly staff. Typical Starbucks pricing.
Great staff
Friendly staff.  Quaint indoor and outdoor seating.  Drive-thru.  Easy order online and pickup in store or curbside.

Customer service is great, but the drinks are a big fail! I always have to go inside and get my drinks remade. They're in such a big rush and just put anything together. I've switched to Dunkin because of this!
great location right by costco, wish they put one on South Blvd so it would be convenient. I order on my own and it was done within 2 minutes.
Quick and efficient service in the drive thru. Friendly staff.
Fast drive-thru. Employees was great. Bumblebee cake pop is good!
Our drinks were ready 10+ minutes after we placed a simple order. Our mistake was coming inside instead of the drive thru or on-line. I appears that lobby orders aren't their priority.

THANK YOU FOR UNDERSTANDING WHAT EXTRA OATMILK MEANS! The other charlotte locations never put enough in it! Adding extra non dairy milk is an expensive modification so thank you for paying attention to it.
The service here was super friendly and fast.

What a great place to get your drink before/after you spend 100's possibly 1000's at Costco. The baristas were cheerful and welcoming. Clean and healthy setting. The coffee, as always, was great. Great interior space and enough space outside to chat while sipping coffee. Highly recommend for all.
Exelent

I didn't catch the name of the gentleman who helped me this morning but he deserves all the stars! I was struggling a little this AM - I spilled my coffee a bit when picking it up, he offered to top my coffee off with another shot and was so kind when helping me clean it up. Kindness goes a long way and as soon as I came to the counter to when I left he was so nice!! This is my favorite location for sure!
Placed an order using the Starbucks app. Easy & quick. Great experience

I like this location, not overcrowded, no passcodes on bathrooms, clean. This one has white chocolate mocha, while other locations are out of stock. They have baby size cups for hot chocolate which is great for kids. So, yes, this location deserves 5 stars. Thank you for good coffee!
The staff was friendly, service was fast and my order was correct!
Good employer
Could be more communicative when food is ready but otherwise good food and service.
Venti pikes place.
Best employee's ever!
Love coming here service always great

The drive thru is horrible. Employers in the drive thru order place are bad, they do not care about the customer and give less than a droplet of attention, thus not hearing the customer's orders. The food is usually good in starbucks, but on this Starbucks it was bad. Not only did they messed up the food, but they hurried with our food as if it was an unimportant task and therefore making the most horrible Starbucks I've ever have gotten the hold of. This Starbucks tasted like nothing, the chocolate was a whole separate thing and the creame was tasteless, not mixed with anything but the very void, the ice was just small ice cubes for the only purpose of making it feel cold at the hold of it. And at last, the employe was not only rude, but made very traumatic and disturbing faces at us and as well with annoyed sounds.

Terrible Starbucks! I'm not usually one to do google reviews but this is a special case. I waited THIRTY mins in the drive thru to just be handed a nitro cold brew WITHOUT sweet foam and with ice in it!!!! I did not receive a refund. I will NEVER come to this starbucks ever again.
This is my store I work at. It is fantastic and all the people here are welcoming and nice.
It's ridiculously cold in this starbucks

This location was my favorite until they started being very rude to me. The Manger shouldn't be a Manger, she doesn't know have to handle situations properly. This location needs better management and customer service. The manger is very rude and doesn't hold her employees accountable for their actions; instead she blames the customers.
This app needs to see I stopped at Starbucks 3 X's in a day, they were all good.  Too much for a caramel latte but ooohh so good.  Just can't help myself.

I stopped in to get a coffee/ drink for myself and my son, a lemon cake and use the restroom. Both drinks were perfect, the lemon cake was tasty and the bathrooms were clean. All employees were pleasant and friendly!

Very horrible experience! After sitting in this specific Starbucks for over 1 hour...a Starbucks that I frequent nearly every day whether by drive thru or walk in...the person ringing me up had the audacity to ask me did I purchase coffee in the Starbucks that day...Jordyn Strickland the store manager  told me this is the policy to ask and I have been coming to Starbucks nearly everyday for at least 7 years and never have I ever been asked did I purchase a coffee in any Starbucks when getting a refill from any Starbucks team member from CT to FL especially when I was sitting in the store the entire time. Jordyn didn't even apologize for my experience! As a manager, she handled the situation very horribly especially because she knows I am always in here! I will not come back to this Starbucks and I am going to sell my Starbucks stock, prices have gone up, value and service have gone down, and consider taking my business elsewhere!
I stop here daily for my latte before work. The service is always friendly and quick.

i got a dragon fruit and the strawberry's were squishy and then I got sick from one of the strawberry and then the lemonade it was kind of bad but mixtures the strawberries and the lemon juice it started to hurt my stomach more
